{
  "texts": [
    "This is an affront to human dignity.",
    "Unsurprisingly, such jobs are characterized by high levels of stress, injury, and illness (Crawford 2021).",
    "Algorithmic management is especially unjust because subjects may not even be employees but independent contractors (Mateescu andNguyen 2019a, 2019b).",
    "Smart machines should be working for people, not people for smart machines (Zuboff 2019).Digitally transformed work cannot be virtuous when it is inhuman, exploitative, and alienating.",
    "Exploitation occurs when work is so chopped up and distributed through a network that low-skilled contractors receive only a pittance for microtasks, without job security or bargaining power (Crawford 2021)."
  ]
}